HEADWORD: Confectionery
<hw>Con*fec"tion*er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Sweetmeats, in general; things prepared and sold by a confectioner;
confections; candies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where candies, sweetmeats, and similar
things are made or sold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confectory</ent>⟦br⟧
